        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer579886600" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12121899955334601746">Khaled Hosseini kills me. His writing seems to wound me as I&apos;m reading his books. I remember when I read the Kite Runner I had to stop for a week or so to psyche myself up to finish it because it made me so sad. (I think I must be getting soft in my old age.) His writing rides a raw edge between nostalgia and pain: you don&apos;t want bad things to happen to his characters because they are already deeply wounded by circumstance. But then another part of me gets inspired to write when I read his work.</span>
  <span id="freeText12121899955334601746" style="display:none">Khaled Hosseini kills me. His writing seems to wound me as I'm reading his books. I remember when I read the Kite Runner I had to stop for a week or so to psyche myself up to finish it because it made me so sad. (I think I must be getting soft in my old age.) His writing rides a raw edge between nostalgia and pain: you don't want bad things to happen to his characters because they are already deeply wounded by circumstance. But then another part of me gets inspired to write when I read his work. I love how he gently handles these flawed, vulnerable creatures. They are pummeled and worked over again and again, but at the same time they are also luminescent with authenticity. <br /><br /><br />It's excellent. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12121899955334601746" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

